---
import Button from "../components/design-system/Button.astro";
import SectionLabel from "../components/design-system/SectionLabel.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../components/design-system/SiteHeader.astro";
import StatusLabel from "../components/design-system/StatusLabel.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const navItems = [
	{ label: "Vision", href: "/#vision" },
	{ label: "Why Mythadis", href: "/why-mythadis/" },
	{ label: "Proof", href: "/proof/" },
	{ label: "Swarm", href: "/#swarm" },
	{ label: "Current State", href: "/#current-state" },
	{ label: "Collaborate", href: "#collaborate" },
];

const timelineItems = [
	"30+ Years",
	"Cloud",
	"Security",
	"Enterprise Architecture",
	"AI",
	"Distributed Intelligence",
	"Mythadis",
];

const invitationAudiences = [
	"Engineers",
	"Researchers",
	"Builders",
	"Skeptics",
	"People willing to challenge assumptions",
];
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Why Mythadis | Mythadis"
	description="Why Mythadis exists, why coordination matters now, and why the project is exploring proof-first infrastructure for human and artificial intelligence."
>
	<div class="ds-shell why-page">
		<SiteHeader
			items={navItems}
			brandLabel="Mythadis"
			brandSubLabel="Swarm"
			status="Private R&D"
		/>

		<main>
			<section class="why-hero" aria-labelledby="page-title">
				<div class="why-hero__copy">
					<StatusLabel tone="amber">Private R&D</StatusLabel>
					<h1 id="page-title">Why Mythadis</h1>
					<div class="origin-lines" aria-label="Origin statement">
						<p>Every technology project begins with an idea.</p>
						<p>Mythadis began with a question.</p>
					</div>
					<p class="mission-question">
						How do we organize intelligence&mdash;human and artificial&mdash;so that together
						we can solve problems that neither could solve alone?
					</p>
				</div>

				<aside class="timeline-panel" aria-label="Bentley's path to Mythadis">
					<ol>
						{timelineItems.map((item) => (
							<li>
								<span>{item}</span>
							</li>
						))}
					</ol>
				</aside>
			</section>

			<section class="reading-section question-section" aria-labelledby="question-title">
				<div class="section-kicker">
					<SectionLabel>The Question</SectionLabel>
				</div>
				<div class="reading-copy">
					<h2 id="question-title">
						How do we organize intelligence&mdash;human and artificial&mdash;so that together
						we can solve problems that neither could solve alone?
					</h2>
					<p>
						That question became larger than AI itself. It pointed past model capability and
						toward the systems around intelligence: how work is discovered, how knowledge moves,
						how claims are checked, and how many participants can contribute without becoming
						noise.
					</p>
					<p class="emphasis-line">
						The limiting factor is not compute. The limiting factor is coordination.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="reading-section experience-section" aria-labelledby="experience-title">
				<div class="section-kicker">
					<SectionLabel>Thirty years</SectionLabel>
				</div>
				<div class="reading-copy">
					<h2 id="experience-title">The same limitation kept appearing in different rooms.</h2>
					<p>
						Bentley spent three decades designing enterprise systems across cloud, security,
						distributed systems, architecture, and large organizations. The details changed.
						The pattern did not.
					</p>
					<p>
						Technology was rarely the biggest limitation. People, organizations, knowledge,
						and communication were. Good systems still failed when the right context could not
						reach the right people at the right time.
					</p>
					<p>
						The problem kept repeating itself: intelligence existed, but it was fragmented.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="reading-section ai-section" aria-labelledby="ai-title">
				<div class="section-kicker">
					<SectionLabel>AI changes everything</SectionLabel>
				</div>
				<div class="reading-copy">
					<h2 id="ai-title">Large language models changed the equation.</h2>
					<p>
						Not because they replaced humans. Because they became another form of intelligence
						that can reason, summarize, propose, remember, and help move work forward.
					</p>
					<p class="question-callout">
						The question is not how humans compete with AI. The question is how human
						intelligence and artificial intelligence should work together.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="principle-band" aria-labelledby="decentralization-title">
				<div>
					<SectionLabel>Why decentralization?</SectionLabel>
					<h2 id="decentralization-title">Resilience is not the same as coordination.</h2>
				</div>
				<div class="principle-lines">
					<p>Centralization creates power.</p>
					<p>Decentralization creates resilience.</p>
					<p>Neither creates coordination by itself.</p>
				</div>
				<p>
					Mythadis explores a different question: how can independent participants collaborate
					without surrendering control?
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="reading-section systems-section" aria-labelledby="systems-title">
				<div class="section-kicker">
					<SectionLabel>Why multiple AI systems?</SectionLabel>
				</div>
				<div class="reading-copy">
					<h2 id="systems-title">The future is unlikely to belong to one model.</h2>
					<p>
						Different AI systems think differently. They carry different strengths, different
						weaknesses, different training, and different viewpoints.
					</p>
					<p>
						A serious coordination layer should not assume that one model, one company, or one
						institution will become the whole answer. The future belongs to many forms of
						intelligence learning how to work together.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="evidence-block" aria-labelledby="evidence-title">
				<SectionLabel>Why evidence?</SectionLabel>
				<h2 id="evidence-title">Evidence before legend.</h2>
				<div class="evidence-grid">
					<p>Intelligence is not enough.</p>
					<p>Consensus is not enough.</p>
					<p>Claims require evidence.</p>
					<p>Disagreement should not disappear.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="why-center" aria-labelledby="why-title">
				<SectionLabel>Why Mythadis?</SectionLabel>
				<h2 id="why-title">
					Mythadis is an attempt to build infrastructure that allows intelligence itself
					to become more organized.
				</h2>
				<div class="center-lines" aria-label="What Mythadis is trying to improve">
					<p>Not simply more powerful.</p>
					<p>Not simply faster.</p>
					<p>Better coordinated.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="reading-section reality-section" aria-labelledby="reality-title">
				<div class="section-kicker">
					<SectionLabel>Current reality</SectionLabel>
				</div>
				<div class="reading-copy">
					<h2 id="reality-title">The work is early, private, and still being proven.</h2>
					<p>
						Mythadis is private R&D. There are early prototypes, a small team, constant
						learning, and large ambitions measured against small daily progress.
					</p>
					<p>
						There is no production network. There is no public Mythadis Agent. The project is
						not claiming that the fabric works at humanity scale. It is trying to prove what
						must be true before that claim would deserve belief.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="invitation-section" id="collaborate" aria-labelledby="invitation-title">
				<div>
					<SectionLabel>The invitation</SectionLabel>
					<h2 id="invitation-title">The first circle.</h2>
					<p>
						The project is looking for people who can pressure-test the architecture, the proof
						discipline, and the mission model before Mythadis asks for broader trust.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="invitation-list" aria-label="Who Mythadis is looking for">
					{invitationAudiences.map((audience) => <span>{audience}</span>)}
				</div>
				<Button href="https://github.com/blanzy-labs">Collaborate with Mythadis</Button>
			</section>

			<section class="future-section" aria-labelledby="future-title">
				<h2 id="future-title">The Future</h2>
				<div class="future-copy">
					<p>The future will not be built by one machine, one company, or one institution.</p>
					<p>It will be built by many forms of intelligence learning how to work together.</p>
					<p>Mythadis is our attempt to help make that possible.</p>
				</div>
				<Button href="https://github.com/blanzy-labs" variant="secondary">
					Collaborate with Mythadis
				</Button>
			</section>
		</main>

		<footer class="why-footer">
			<p>Mythadis coordinates intelligence&mdash;not just computation.</p>
			<a href="/">Return to the vision</a>
		</footer>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	h1,
	h2,
	h3,
	p {
		text-wrap: pretty;
	}

	h1,
	h2,
	h3 {
		margin: 0;
		font-family: var(--ds-font-display);
		letter-spacing: 0;
	}

	.why-page {
		--reading-max: 820px;
	}

	.why-hero {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(260px, 340px);
		gap: 64px;
		align-items: start;
		min-height: calc(100svh - 84px);
		padding: 70px 0 118px;
	}

	.why-hero__copy {
		max-width: 920px;
	}

	.why-hero h1 {
		margin-top: 26px;
		font-size: clamp(4.6rem, 10.4vw, 11rem);
		line-height: 0.84;
	}

	.origin-lines {
		display: grid;
		gap: 8px;
		margin-top: 44px;
		color: var(--ds-ink-soft);
		font-family: var(--ds-font-display);
		font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 2.5vw, 2.25rem);
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.08;
	}

	.origin-lines p,
	.mission-question,
	.reading-copy p,
	.principle-band p,
	.evidence-grid p,
	.center-lines p,
	.invitation-section p,
	.future-copy p,
	.why-footer p {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.origin-lines p:last-child {
		color: var(--ds-ink);
	}

	.mission-question {
		max-width: 880px;
		margin-top: 40px;
		padding-top: 30px;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--ds-line-strong);
		color: var(--ds-ink);
		font-family: var(--ds-font-display);
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.4vw, 4.6rem);
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 0.98;
	}

	.timeline-panel {
		position: sticky;
		top: 28px;
		padding-top: 11px;
	}

	.timeline-panel ol {
		position: relative;
		display: grid;
		gap: 0;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0 0 0 24px;
		list-style: none;
	}

	.timeline-panel ol::before {
		position: absolute;
		top: 6px;
		bottom: 8px;
		left: 5px;
		width: 1px;
		content: "";
		background: linear-gradient(var(--ds-blue), var(--ds-mint));
		box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(66, 217, 255, 0.34);
	}

	.timeline-panel li {
		position: relative;
		padding: 0 0 28px;
		color: var(--ds-ink-soft);
		font-family: var(--ds-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
	}

	.timeline-panel li::before {
		position: absolute;
		top: 4px;
		left: -24px;
		width: 11px;
		height: 11px;
		content: "";
		border: 1px solid var(--ds-line-strong);
		background: var(--ds-void);
		box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(66, 217, 255, 0.2);
		transform: rotate(45deg);
	}

	.timeline-panel li:last-child {
		padding-bottom: 0;
		color: var(--ds-ink);
		font-family: var(--ds-font-display);
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		text-transform: none;
		letter-spacing: 0;
	}

	.reading-section {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(150px, 260px) minmax(0, var(--reading-max));
		gap: 42px;
		padding: 0 0 112px;
	}

	.section-kicker {
		padding-top: 8px;
	}

	.reading-copy {
		display: grid;
		gap: 24px;
	}

	.reading-copy h2 {
		max-width: 16ch;
		font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4.7vw, 5rem);
		line-height: 0.96;
	}

	.reading-copy p,
	.principle-band > p,
	.invitation-section p {
		color: var(--ds-ink-soft);
		font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.5vw, 1.22rem);
		line-height: 1.72;
	}

	.emphasis-line,
	.question-callout {
		padding-top: 22px;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--ds-line);
		color: var(--ds-ink) !important;
		font-family: var(--ds-font-display);
		font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.7vw, 2.35rem) !important;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.1 !important;
	}

	.principle-band {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.78fr) minmax(300px, 1fr);
		gap: 34px 54px;
		align-items: end;
		margin: 0 0 112px;
		padding: 78px 0;
		border-block: 1px solid var(--ds-line-strong);
		background:
			linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(66, 217, 255, 0.08), transparent 36%),
			linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(2, 7, 10, 0.16), rgba(2, 7, 10, 0.48));
	}

	.principle-band h2 {
		max-width: 640px;
		font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 6vw, 6.4rem);
		line-height: 0.9;
	}

	.principle-lines {
		display: grid;
		gap: 14px;
	}

	.principle-lines p {
		padding-top: 14px;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--ds-line);
		color: var(--ds-ink);
		font-family: var(--ds-font-display);
		font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 2.7vw, 2.35rem);
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.06;
	}

	.principle-band > p {
		grid-column: 2;
		max-width: 680px;
	}

	.evidence-block {
		margin: 0 0 112px;
		padding: 86px 0;
		border-block: 1px solid var(--ds-line-strong);
	}

	.evidence-block h2 {
		max-width: 980px;
		font-size: clamp(4.2rem, 10vw, 10.6rem);
		line-height: 0.84;
	}

	.evidence-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
		gap: 0;
		margin-top: 54px;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--ds-line);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ds-line);
	}

	.evidence-grid p {
		min-height: 150px;
		padding: 22px;
		border-right: 1px solid var(--ds-line);
		color: var(--ds-ink-soft);
		font-family: var(--ds-font-display);
		font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.2vw, 2.1rem);
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.06;
	}

	.evidence-grid p:last-child {
		border-right: 0;
		color: var(--ds-mint);
	}

	.why-center {
		display: grid;
		align-content: center;
		min-height: 82svh;
		padding: 44px 0 128px;
	}

	.why-center h2 {
		max-width: 1100px;
		font-size: clamp(3.2rem, 7.8vw, 8.2rem);
		line-height: 0.9;
	}

	.center-lines {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 18px;
		max-width: 920px;
		margin: 48px 0 0 auto;
	}

	.center-lines p {
		padding-top: 18px;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--ds-line);
		color: var(--ds-ink-soft);
		font-family: var(--ds-font-display);
		font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.2vw, 1.9rem);
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.08;
	}

	.center-lines p:last-child {
		color: var(--ds-ink);
	}

	.invitation-section {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(260px, 0.58fr);
		gap: 42px;
		align-items: start;
		padding: 0 0 128px;
	}

	.invitation-section h2 {
		font-size: clamp(3.2rem, 7vw, 7rem);
		line-height: 0.88;
	}

	.invitation-section p {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin-top: 28px;
	}

	.invitation-list {
		display: grid;
		gap: 10px;
		padding-top: 10px;
	}

	.invitation-list span {
		padding: 13px 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ds-line);
		color: var(--ds-ink-soft);
		font-family: var(--ds-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.74rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
	}

	.invitation-section :global(.ds-button) {
		width: fit-content;
	}

	.future-section {
		display: grid;
		justify-items: start;
		min-height: 82svh;
		padding: 98px 0 128px;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--ds-line-strong);
	}

	.future-section h2 {
		color: var(--ds-blue);
		font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 1.8vw, 1.5rem);
		line-height: 1;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
	}

	.future-copy {
		display: grid;
		gap: 28px;
		max-width: 1060px;
		margin: 52px 0 42px;
	}

	.future-copy p {
		color: var(--ds-ink);
		font-family: var(--ds-font-display);
		font-size: clamp(2.65rem, 5.8vw, 6.8rem);
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 0.94;
	}

	.future-copy p:last-child {
		color: var(--ds-mint);
	}

	.why-footer {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 20px;
		padding: 34px 0 46px;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--ds-line);
		color: var(--ds-ink-muted);
		font-size: 0.86rem;
	}

	.why-footer a {
		color: var(--ds-ink-soft);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ds-line-strong);
	}

	@media (max-width: 1040px) {
		.why-hero,
		.reading-section,
		.principle-band,
		.invitation-section {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.why-hero {
			min-height: auto;
		}

		.timeline-panel {
			position: relative;
			top: auto;
			max-width: 520px;
		}

		.principle-band > p {
			grid-column: auto;
		}

		.evidence-grid,
		.center-lines {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 680px) {
		.why-hero {
			gap: 42px;
			padding: 38px 0 82px;
		}

		.why-hero h1 {
			font-size: clamp(3.25rem, 19vw, 5.7rem);
			line-height: 0.88;
		}

		.mission-question {
			font-size: clamp(1.85rem, 10vw, 3.25rem);
		}

		.reading-section {
			gap: 18px;
			padding-bottom: 82px;
		}

		.reading-copy h2,
		.principle-band h2,
		.invitation-section h2 {
			font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 12vw, 3.7rem);
		}

		.principle-band,
		.evidence-block {
			margin-bottom: 82px;
			padding: 58px 0;
		}

		.evidence-block h2,
		.why-center h2 {
			font-size: clamp(3rem, 16vw, 5.3rem);
		}

		.evidence-grid,
		.center-lines {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.evidence-grid p {
			min-height: 104px;
			border-right: 0;
			border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ds-line);
		}

		.evidence-grid p:last-child {
			border-bottom: 0;
		}

		.why-center,
		.future-section {
			min-height: auto;
			padding-bottom: 92px;
		}

		.center-lines {
			margin-left: 0;
		}

		.invitation-section {
			padding-bottom: 92px;
		}

		.invitation-section :global(.ds-button),
		.future-section :global(.ds-button) {
			width: 100%;
		}

		.future-copy p {
			font-size: clamp(2.35rem, 13vw, 4.6rem);
		}

		.why-footer {
			flex-direction: column;
		}
	}
</style>
